          <p>The entire Fort Knox facility is enclosed with a gated perimeter. Access requires your personal code — passersby and non-customers cannot enter. This is a baseline security standard missing at many Vernal storage options.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-card">
          <div class="security-icon">🔥</div>
          <h3>Fire Detection System</h3>
          <p>An active fire detection system monitors the facility. Most budget storage facilities in Vernal have no fire detection at all. At Fort Knox it's standard — no upgrade required, no additional fee.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-card">
          <div class="security-icon">🐭</div>
          <h3>Mouse-Proof Steel Construction</h3>
          <p>All Fort Knox containers are sealed all-steel shipping containers. No wood framing. No floor gaps. No entry points for rodents, insects, or vermin of any kind. Wood-frame units in Vernal can be physically chewed through — steel cannot.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-card">
          <div class="security-icon">💪</div>
          <h3>Hardened Steel Walls</h3>
          <p>Cor-Ten steel shipping container walls are significantly harder to breach than the thin-gauge doors and panels used at traditional self-storage facilities. The same material used to ship cargo across oceans protects your belongings here in Vernal.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-card">
          <div class="security-icon">🚗</div>
          <h3>Drive-Up Access</h3>
          <p>Pull your vehicle directly to the container door — no indoor corridors, no elevators, no loading docks shared with strangers. This also means you load and unload in full view of the entry gate, adding a natural deterrent to opportunistic activity.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="security-card">
          <div class="security-icon">📞</div>
          <h3>Direct Owner Contact — 24/7</h3>
          <p>James Richards, the owner, is reachable by call or text 24/7 at 435-828-7710. If you have a concern about your unit, access, or anything else at the facility, you're not calling a national call center — you're calling the owner directly.</p>
